A webhook allows Jira to notify external services when certain events happen (like progress updates). Itâ€™s a way to connect Jira with other tools like Slack or CI/CD systems.
 
âž¡ï¸ ð™Žð™¡ð™–ð™˜ð™  ð˜¼ð™ªð™©ð™¤ð™¢ð™–ð™©ð™žð™¤ð™£ ð™Žð™©ð™šð™¥ð™¨ (ð™›ð™¤ð™§ ð™§ð™šð™˜ð™šð™žð™«ð™žð™£ð™œ ð™¥ð™§ð™¤ð™œð™§ð™šð™¨ð™¨ ð™£ð™¤ð™©ð™žð™›ð™žð™˜ð™–ð™©ð™žð™¤ð™£ð™¨):
1. Go to Jira Settings > System > Webhooks.
2. Create a new webhook with the Slack Incoming Webhook URL.
3. Select events like "Issue Created", "Issue Updated", etc.
4. Test the webhook to ensure Slack receives updates.
5. Customize your Slack message formatting using JSON payloads for clarity.
